Ondo State Governor, Rotimi Akeredolu, SAN, has described the former governor of Ogun State and Senator representing Ogun Central Senatorial district, Senator Ibikunle Amosun, as a dependable brother and an unassuming servant of the people. He said Amosun’s commitment to nation-building and his passion for service are unparalleled. Akeredolu said this while congratulating Amosun on his 64th Birthday. This was contained in a statement signed by his Chief Press Secretary, Richard Olatunde. The statement read, ”As you celebrate your birthday, we salute your dedication and commitment to nation-building. “Your passion for service is unparalleled. As a former two-term governor and Senator of the Federal Republic, you have shown your dedication to public service both at the state and federal levels. “Your successes in various fields of human endeavour have built an enduring legacy for you. Having contributed immensely to the development and growth of your state, Ogun and the country, yours is a meritorious service.” Akeredolu prayed to God to grant the lawmaker long life and good health to continue in the service of the nation and humanity. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com